{"change_summary":"Removed unrelated Claude process-backend debugging scaffolding from `src/adapters/process_backend.rs`, stopped passing the unconditional `--debug-file` argument, and removed the tracked `result` symlink from version control while adding `result` to `.gitignore`. No changes were needed to the approved artifact-metadata fix itself.","outstanding_risks":[],"steps":[{"description":"Confirmed the remaining out-of-scope branch changes were the two Claude JSON-parse `eprintln!` blocks, the unconditional `--debug-file` wiring in `src/adapters/process_backend.rs`, and the tracked `result` symlink.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Removed the two debug `eprintln!` calls and the `debug_file` / `--debug-file` argument construction from `src/adapters/process_backend.rs`, preserving the surrounding error handling and Claude command setup.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Stopped tracking the local `result` symlink with `git rm --cached result` and added `result` to `.gitignore` so future local Nix build outputs stay out of version control.","order":2,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Revalidated the branch with the Nix Rust toolchain using `cargo check` and the full `cargo test --lib` suite after the cleanup.","order":3,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["Static inspection of `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:70-96` shows the Claude envelope/result parse failures now map directly to `ProcessBackendAdapter::invocation_failed(...)` without the temporary `eprintln!` stderr dumps.","Static inspection of `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:420-431` shows the Claude CLI argument list no longer constructs a `debug_file` path or appends `--debug-file`, restoring the normal subprocess invocation shape.","`git diff -- src/adapters/process_backend.rs .gitignore` shows exactly the cleanup changes: 19 debug-only lines removed from `process_backend.rs` and `result` added to `.gitignore`.","`git diff --cached -- result` shows the tracked `result` symlink is staged for removal from version control, while the new `.gitignore` entry keeps the local symlink from reappearing as an untracked change.","`nix develop -c cargo check` succeeded; the only diagnostics were the pre-existing unused `spawned` warnings in `src/contexts/conformance_spec/runner.rs:108`, `src/contexts/conformance_spec/runner.rs:124`, and `src/contexts/conformance_spec/runner.rs:179`.","`nix develop -c cargo test --lib` succeeded with 86 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored; this run included `contexts::agent_execution::service::tests::invoke_preserves_adapter_reported_backend_and_model_metadata` and `contexts::workflow_composition::final_review::tests::persisted_artifacts_use_envelope_metadata_not_resolved_target`."]}